commit.message: Moving the license README snippet to LICENSE file

Reference the internal PaginatedCSVRenderer instead of instructing
users to write their own.
Support Non UTF-8 Encoding Parsing
Only test Django 1.8 against pre-3.7 versions of DRF
Use tox-travis to help with python versions on Travis
Update Travis test versions and tox configuration
Added tests for generator support in CSVStreamingRenderer

Allow Generator data in CSVStreamingRenderer

CSVStreamingRenderer does not support a data source of a Generator object, but the Renderer works properly with it as tabelize works as a generator along with CSVStreamingRenderer itself.  This makes it so that if the data passed in is a Generator object, it does not need to go through the conversion to a list.

commit.message: Added django.contrib.contenttypes to testsettings.INSTALLED_APPS

Include a paginated renderer as part of the app
https://github.com/mjumbewu/django-rest-framework-csv/issues/17

Add labeled headers to csvs with no data (#58)

CSVs with no data should still use header labels
This change mirrors label behavior that occurs when there is data
Show the master branch build status in the README
Import settings from renderers (for DEFAULT_CHARSET)
Add a simple example app
Prefer header argument over attribute on data in renderer
Use 'header' instead of 'data_header' in tablize

Return header row if supplied, even if there's no data

Resolves #32

Consistently pass bytes into parsers and expect bytes out of renderers

Resolves #43
make it work in production (via wsgi)
dependencies
cleanup
use unicodecsv and make parsing more robust
Drop Django 1.7, add Django 1.10 to tests

Modify tablize to properly stream data for the renderer

From the `CSVRenderer.tablize` docstring:

> If there is a header provided to tablize it will efficiently yield each
> row as needed. If no header is provided, tablize will need to process
> each row in the data in order to construct a complete header. Thus, if
> you have a lot of data and want to stream it, you should probably
> provide a header to the renderer (using the `header` attribute, or via
> the `renderer_context`).

Closes #16, closes #46
Remove deprecated usage of writer_opts from tests
